updates.update_content:
FTLOS fans;
I can’t believe it’s been just over a year since the successful completion of our Kickstarter campaign. Boy how time flies when you’re working on For The Love Of Spock!
As of last week, we have officially delivered the finished film to our distributor! While there’s still a few steps left before our final release in September, it’s exciting to think that we’re finally reaching the finish line! (Whew!!)

We were wrong last time - this is the penultimate update for Darklands: First Edition II, as (despite Florus not really being a part of this project) we included him here anyway...
This week we have:
sculpt work in progress images from Juan Navarro Pérez;
a list of what miniatures are currently being sent in their various waves;

It's the penultimate update for Darklands: First Edition II, and the first for a long while; this project is almost done!
This week we have:
sculpt work in progress images from Yannick Hennebo;
a list of what miniatures are currently being sent in their various waves;
Wave 8 and 9 shipments are ongoing and will be for some time, and shipments for Wave 10 are well underway, with some items from Wave 11 going too.

For the first time in a  while, It's Mierceday here at Darklands: First Edition II - possibly even the second-but-last update for this project, at least in terms of new miniatures to show!
This week we have:
sculpt work in progress images from Martin Lavat;
a list of what miniatures are currently being sent in their various waves;
Wave 8 and 9 shipments are ongoing and will be for some time, and shipments for Wave 10 are well underway, with some items from Wave 11 going too.

It's Mierceday, Miercenaries, so it's time for an update on what we here at Mierce have been up to!
This week we have:
sculpt work in progress images from Yannick Hennebo and Stéphane Simon;
a list of what miniatures are currently being sent in their various waves;

It's a fine day for an update, so why don't we give you one?
This week we have:
sculpt work in progress images from Yannick Hennebo, Martin Lavat and Stéphane Simon;
a list of what miniatures are currently being sent in their various waves;

